# Analysis of "discussion" Discord Channel

## 1. Summary
The discussion primarily revolves around ElizaOS ecosystem development and the AI16Z token. cjft shared technical details about ongoing development, mentioning they're shipping 500k LoC weekly with baby AGI assistance. Key upcoming products include Launchpad, login with Eliza, hosted inference, Eliza A2A network, desktop/mobile apps, and robots. The A2A (Agent-to-Agent) network will be based on token fees for broadcast, bid, and receive actions between agents and humans, potentially creating validator/oracle nodes for staking AI16Z tokens. The team is developing autocoder functionality (referencing github.com/elizaos-plugins/plugin-autocoder) that allows creating plugins through natural language. Community members expressed concerns about the token's price decline (90%+ drawdown) and the suspended X/Twitter account, which is hampering marketing efforts. The team indicated they're working on V2 announcements and waiting for X account restoration before a major marketing push.

## 2. FAQ
Q: What will be the benefits of the A2A network? (asked by Kylie) A: It will create token fees and bring income to the Eliza ecosystem through broadcast, bid, receive actions between agents and humans. Similar to ACP but not bound to any framework. (answered by cjft)
Q: How can we get CLI elizaOS login? (asked by Kylie) A: It's not out yet, TBD. (answered by cjft)
Q: Do we have any limitations in plugin-creation scope? (asked by Kylie) A: No limits. (answered by cjft)
Q: Can Ai agent from Eliza help with data entry? (asked by VOLDISGOD) A: Unanswered
Q: What are the plans to bring back users to autofun product? (asked by Kylie) A: No have to wait and see. (answered by cjft)
Q: Where can I use eliza chat framework? (asked by ElizaBAOðŸŒŸ) A: https://eliza.how/ (answered by cjft)
Q: Where can I get a guide on how to build ai agents for slow learners? (asked by 3on_.) A: Check #useful-links channel and dev school videos. (answered by open24hrs)

# Discord Chat Analysis for ðŸ’»-tech-support

## 1. Summary
The chat primarily revolves around troubleshooting ElizaOS plugins and implementation issues. Key technical discussions include:

- OS compatibility issues with ElizaOS, with a user experiencing problems on macOS 15.5 but successful builds on Ubuntu
- Plugin-knowledge tab visibility bug identified and acknowledged for fix in version 1.0.13
- Telegram plugin configuration issues in group chats, resolved by adjusting privacy settings with BotFather
- Twitter plugin updates requiring API keys due to X platform restrictions
- Ollama configuration problems when replacing local-ai
- Bootstrap plugin errors related to missing required fields
- Issues with the latest ElizaOS 1.0.13 where the starter plugin's hello world action gets stuck without responding
- A fix was implemented in PR #5296 for the hello world action issue, though some users continued to experience problems even after applying the fix

The team released ElizaOS v1.0.13 with various fixes and updates to plugins.

## 2. FAQ
Q: How do I use Ollama configuration instead of it automatically using local AI? (asked by bolt1king) A: Remove local-ia from plugins list, leave only ollama plugin (answered by 0xbbjoker)
Q: Is the current latest "elizaos/plugin-twitter": "1.0.9" likely to be banned? (asked by alerios) A: No it's not gonna be banned, just requires API keys now, it's fine long term (answered by cjft)
Q: Why isn't my Telegram bot working in group chats? (asked by Luke ðŸ‡¦ðŸ‡º) A: Check its privacy settings with the botfather (answered by Odilitime)
Q: Why won't my agent post tweets autonomously despite responding to mentions? (asked by elle) A: You might need a paid Twitter plan for some endpoints (answered by Niann)
